# Validator / Curator

Validators are humans who turn raw market intelligence into actionable picks for subscribers. The platform's core differentiator is human + AI hybrid â€” not pure algorithmic, not pure newsletter.

## Personas

| Validator | Persona | Scope |
|-----------|---------|-------|
| Founder | `founder` | Self; can publish anything |
| Twisted Slice | `twisted_slice` | Hedge fund analyst; primary external validator for v1 |
| (future) | `marketplace_validator` | Year 2 â€” multiple validators, revenue share |

## Pseudonym enforcement (HARD RULE)

- **Real names/emails of validators are NEVER exposed in user-facing artifacts** (UI, marketing copy, public scorecards, RSS feeds, exported PDFs, webhooks to subscribers).
- Real identifiers live ONLY in:
  - `PICKS_TRUSTED_SENDERS` env var (server-side, never read by client code)
  - A new encrypted `validator_identity` table for the v1 picks pipeline (admin-only access via `OWNER` role + audit log; **to be implemented**)
- All UI references use the validator pseudonym/display handle (`twisted_slice`, "Twisted Slice").
- Code review checklist: grep for any real validator email, name, or other identifier in any user-facing output (UI strings, marketing copy, exports, public scorecards, RSS, webhooks to subscribers). Use the `PICKS_TRUSTED_SENDERS` env-var values as the canonical denylist. If any match is found, block the PR.

## Picks pipeline state machine

```
DRAFT -> APPROVED -> PUBLISHED
  |          |
REJECTED   REJECTED (post-approve, withdrawn)
```

- `DRAFT`: parser output, awaiting validator review
- `APPROVED`: validator clicked approve; queued for publish
- `PUBLISHED`: visible to subscribers per their tier; webhook fired
- `REJECTED`: not for publication

State transitions are audited in a dedicated audit table (planned name: `pick_audit_log`; **to be implemented as part of the v1 picks pipeline**) with actor, timestamp, before/after.

## Source attribution

Every published item carries:

| Field | Required | Purpose |
|-------|----------|---------|
| `validator` | yes | Who curated it (`twisted_slice`, `founder`) |
| `original_author` | when forwarded | Original analyst (e.g., "Keith McCullough / Hedgeye") |
| `source_type` | yes | `ORIGINAL_ANALYSIS` / `FORWARDED_RECAP` / `EDITED_FORWARD` / `LLM_DRAFT_VALIDATED` |
| `inbound_email_id` | when from email | Foreign key to `inbound_email` table for traceability |
| `attribution_required` | when quoting | If `true`, UI must show source badge prominently |

## LLM parser behavior

- **Polymorphic schema selection** by gpt-4o-mini at parse time; full extraction by gpt-4o
- Templates: `single_stock_bullets`, `single_stock_research_note`, `macro_recap_with_position_changes`, `daily_market_recap_narrative`, `mixed`
- Vision (gpt-4o vision) for chart captioning ONLY for trusted senders (cost gate)
- Cross-email signal linking: vector similarity + symbolic level matching; surfaces "this reinforces email X from Y days ago" but does NOT auto-merge â€” validator decides

## Tier-gated publish

| Tier | What they see |
|------|---------------|
| Free | Picks 24h after publish; watchlist add only |
| Pro | Real-time picks; email/SMS alerts; one-click execute (paper or live); autotrade per `feature_catalog` |
| Pro+ | + `SignalToOrder` auto-execute where enabled; bracket orders; tax-aware exits; native chat |
| Quant Desk | + Trade Copy (mirror Twisted Slice's published picks automatically) |

## Costs

- Per-tier LLM budget caps (D87) enforced via `LLMGateway`
- Vision calls degraded first when budget tight
- Postmortem budget overruns logged in `KNOWLEDGE.md` as `R##` entries
